
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `apt-get` baraye gereftan (install), paak kardan (remove), va update kardan narmafzar-ha (software) dar system-haye Debian va Ubuntu estefade mishavad.  Yek rah-e asan baraye modiriat narmafzar-ha az command line ast.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `sudo apt-get update` --> 🔄 Gereftan akharin etela'at az manabe narmafzari. (Update kardane list-e narmafzar-ha)
    🔹 `sudo apt-get upgrade` --> ⬆️ Update kardane hameye narmafzare haye nasb shode be akharin version.
    🔹 `sudo apt-get install [esm-e-narmafzar]` --> 📦 Nasb kardane yek narmafzar. (Install kardane yek barname)
    🔹 `sudo apt-get remove [esm-e-narmafzar]` --> 🗑️ Paak kardane yek narmafzar, ama config file-hash mimoonan.
    🔹 `sudo apt-get purge [esm-e-narmafzar]` --> 💣 Paak kardane yek narmafzar hamrah ba hameye config file-hash.
    🔹 `sudo apt-get autoremove` --> 🧹 Paak kardane package-haye zaedi ke dige estefade nemishan.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ sudo apt-get update

    🔹 Gereftan akharin etela'at az repo-ha.

    $ sudo apt-get install firefox

    🔹 Nasb kardane barname firefox.

    $ sudo apt-get remove firefox

    🔹 Hazf kardane barname firefox az system.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get upgrade

    🔹 Aval list-e narmafzar-haro update mikone, bad hameye narmafzar-haye ghadimi ro be akharin version update mikone.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `apt-get` command is used to retrieve (install), remove, and update software packages on Debian and Ubuntu-based systems. It's a convenient way to manage software from the command line.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `sudo apt-get update` --> 🔄 Retrieve the latest package information from the configured sources. (Updates package lists)
    🔹 `sudo apt-get upgrade` --> ⬆️ Upgrade all installed packages to their newest versions.
    🔹 `sudo apt-get install [package-name]` --> 📦 Install a new software package.
    🔹 `sudo apt-get remove [package-name]` --> 🗑️ Remove a software package, but keeps configuration files.
    🔹 `sudo apt-get purge [package-name]` --> 💣 Remove a software package along with its configuration files.
    🔹 `sudo apt-get autoremove` --> 🧹 Remove automatically all unused dependencies.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ sudo apt-get update

    🔹 Update the package lists from the repositories.

    $ sudo apt-get install firefox

    🔹 Install the firefox browser.

    $ sudo apt-get remove firefox

    🔹 Uninstall the firefox browser from the system.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get upgrade

    🔹 First update the package list, then upgrade all outdated packages to the newest version.
